item.title: He Proposed
item.dc:creator: 4104wpczar
item.content:encoded:
On our trip to Yosemite, Avery stepped away, got down on one knee, and asked me to marry him. I was so awestruck, confused and surprised at the same time as he stood there ring in hand. It took a moment to process, I reached for the ring, and Avery reminded me that I hadn't said yes. With tears in my eyes I shouted:
"Yes! Yes of course! Yes!"
